product_title: Monopod 500 Floor Standing Monopod
review_body:
I had/have a cheaper and lighter monopod. This Canon is much higher quality - especially in stability when extended. I do have the problem of the ball not locking tightly (30D & 450D various lenses) but haven't tried sanding it yet. I might try sanding the plastic cup area first and hope that cures the problem up. Excellent unit, little heavier than the cheaper versions but not so much as to be cumbersome. It's easy to spin on and off the camera so you might consider buying only it to see if you really need the easy removable head. Is it worth the extra bucks? Depends upon how you use it and if you use a Canon. Always looks neat to have all Canon gear. LOL
No LOL now. The head where the camera mounts has become loose - there's enough slop that the camera can shift unless you're really concentrating on holding it in position. This is NOT the ball slipping but the thumbwheel that screws into the camera base.
Just spoke to Canon, minimal warranty and NO PARTS IN STOCK only sell complete units.
So I have to pin this head in a couple of directions to take the slop out.
No, I'm not rough on my gear.
Went from a 4 (due to slipping ball mount) to a 2 (lack of repair parts)
caveat emptor

product_title: Bushnell Banner Multi-X Reticle Riflescope with 6" Eye Relief, 3-9x 40mm
review_headline: broke after several trips to the range
review_body:
I purchased this scope along with the [[ASIN:B000R7872Y Aim Sports M44/Mosin Nagant 91/30 Scope Mount (Short)]] and a [[ASIN:B001WJ67S2 AccuShot Premium 1-Inch Weaver Style See-Thru Medium Profile Rings]].

The scope is just the right length for my rifle. It sticks out far enough that it's no problem sighting it in, but in far enough that it's no trouble cycleing the bolt.

It also works well for my S&W m&p 15-22.

UPDATED 1/6/2014:

After several trips to the range, this scope would no longer hold center. I was shooting at a target 50 feet away and the POI were about 6\\" appart, and not grouped at all.
This scope was being used on a .22, so high recoil is not the problem.
Also, this scope was not dropped, or abused in any way; I also don't think it was damaged in shipping.

I'm going to try to return this, because I think this scope was a lemon.
I will update when I get to try the replacement.

product_title: Coleman Signature Instant Dome 5 Tent
review_body:
Got this, (I don't recall it being called "signature" though, it looks identical but I think the color scheme might be switched around, at any rate it is the single hub design), at Costco, for $79! This is a very good recreational tent, really can't complain after one overnight use with my 2 kids. It is a great size for 2 or 3 people, more than that and you're cramming in. Fit and finish are very nice, and when pitched and staked, it is a very sturdy tent. Not at all useful for backpacking any real distance, but easy for car camping or a short walk in. I saw one review complaining about moisture inside the tent, to combat this, you can either leave the windows and door open, or cease to breathe. It's condensed water vapor from your breath. It dried out in less than five minutes when I opened the tent up in the morning.

First setup took 10 minutes to figure the thing out, but I believe now 60 seconds would be realistic (to set it up, another couple minutes to put stakes up). To set it up, you unfold it, straighten out the legs until they pop straight (no buttons or anything, and there are soft pads over the joints, i'm guessing they are there to protect the tent when it is folded up), the last pole over the door can be put into its sleeve before you straighten it out. Make sure all the little hooks from the tent are around the poles, they were already on on my tent. Then extend the ends of the four corner poles. They telescope out, which raises the tent. I didn't see the telescoping parts for a while and the instructions are bare bones, it wasn't obvious.

I had never seen the self rolling windows before, and I really don't understand what the instructions are trying to picture, but basically they are flat springs that work like slap wrap wristbands. They come rolled up in the stake bag, I assumed they were tape or patches or something. To use them You open the Velcro opening under each window, straighten the roller spring completely, and push it up the channel. Then when you want to roll the window up, you just push it in a little bit to set the spring into action and let

Also, you are unable to be far from the TV due to the cables if you are showing pictures or trying to browse through things on your phone. If I have perfect reception from the antenna to the first tv why is the amplified signal down the line not as good? This is not the first amplifier I have had and none of them really work. Your signal will only be as good as the antenna you have installed. Just place your antenna in the best possible place and move it around until you get the signal you want. Have someone to assist you. This may mean you'll have to be nice to your wife until the signal is achieved.

product_title: Monster Cable HDMI1000HD4M MC1000HD-4M Ultra-High Speed HDMI Cable
review_headline: Cable Can Only Perform and Be as Good as the Equipment it's Connected To
review_body: I understand all the opinions of the rocket scientists out there about 1's and 0's and everything. To a degree they are correct. Honestly though, if indeed this were that simple, then why would there be different HDMI cables offered from the same manufacturer? I suppose for the sucker like me! Sorry but no way! Let's start with this: the performance of the cable, materially perceptible performance anyway, will depend almost entirely on the equipment it is connected to. I'm sorry (again), but a cable is not going to make a bad DVD player (bad chipsets, interlacing capability etc.), or a cheap discount flat screen significantly better. The poor performance is inherent in the equipment itself. Also, you are highly unlikely to see any significant difference on a TV smaller than 50\\". I have a top end DVD player, Sony PS3 (for Blu-Ray), 2 Hi-Def cable/sat boxes with HDMI output (I can't control the quality level here) and the latest Pioneer Kuro 60\\" screen and let me tell you, the image is popping out of the screen with ever greater clarity and colors. Most importantly, I see less of the 'jittery' stuff (in layman's terms) than I did before, with already good equipment. So the point is, to take advantage of what 'faster' cables have to offer (which is one of the key things this cable offers with the way it is constructed), certain pre-conditions have to exist. Without these, many people probably are wasting their money...but it works for me!

review_body:

Other devices (laptops and tablets) on my wifi did NOT disconnect. For the last few weeks, it's been unusable - disconnects constantly, and doesn't even remember my longish password so that I have to use the remote to type this is almost every day.

Why did I ever buy this product rather than using a reliable roku player? And, rokus (even the high-end roku models) are cheaper ! I'd strongly suggest that you save yourself problems and not buy this product.

product_title: Samsung 1080p LED HDTV
review_body:
Let me start out by saying that I'm a bit of a TV snob. I have the latest/greatest Panasonic plasma (the VT60) in my den. This is my bedroom TV and it replaced an older 720p Toshiba. I'm amazed at the difference. While it can't possibly equal the black levels of the VT60 or its color depth or nuance it's damn good. Razor sharp images, great white levels, excellent flesh tones and good viewing angles (long a pet peeve of mine with LCD/LED's). I want to make particular note of the built-in speakers. Way better than the outgoing Toshiba and much better than the speakers on the VT60. As we all know, sound quality is one area in which flat panels have compromised. Sometimes to the point that the consumer is almost forced to go to an external speaker solution (as I did with the VT60). Not so here. The sound quality is actually well above average and has a resonable amount of bass for such a small system. Is it audiophile quality? Heck no! But it's great for everyday viewing/listening and can even do justice to music with wide dynamic range. While most flat panels give their speakers 2 or 4 watt amplifiers, this has two 10 watt amplifiers built in. This makes a huge difference at moderate (to louder) levels and keeps things sounding clean and non-distorted. For a TV costing well under $500 this unit is incredible. If you want bells and whistles or a smart TV you're going to want to looks elsewhere. If you want a TV that serves as a monitor for your cable/fios feed then this is your answer.

BTW for those of you concerned about the \\"outsourced panel\\" issue let me say that I have the HS03 version (made by Sharp I'm told). It really is superb so have no worries. ;-)

product_title: Pet Tornado
review_headline: too short to be fun or a good illustration
review_body:
The toy is an acrylic glass cylinder with water and bubbles inside. If you make the water rotate, the bubbles will first distribute over the entire cylinder, them go up and concentrate along the cylinder axis (the tornado), before entirely concentrating at the top. The phase in which that tornado-like formation in the middle happens is very short, perhaps two or three seconds; you have to be looking for it to see it. It is to short to tell your children `here look at this, it looks like a tornado':
before the children look, the effect is already gone. Children can still have some fun with it, as they can have with anything that moves, but as educational toy it is disappointing.

product_title: Roll Up Piano - LED Digital Display 37 Keys Roll-Up Electronic Piano Keyboard
review_headline: ordered something else and got this
review_body:
Ordered a cometely different item that WAS supposed to have the adapter and got this instead. Amazon customer service made good on the problem. Even so, after receiving this, the instructinos are laughable and indeed don't have specs for purchasing a seperate adapter. Radio Shack or similar doesn't carry specific adapters anymore and you have to invest in a pricey 'universal one'.

--- Haven't tried it yet, but no AC ADAPTER is included. Just the 'JACK' which indicates \\"DC6V\\". AC adapter needs to be purchased separately and adds to overall cost. Instructions state 4-AA batteries are reqd. Listed features on outside of box state 3-AAA are reqd. The winner? Curtain#1, which is 4-AA batteries. I honestly don't imagine this is a `mobile' item for us, (wouldn't want to show up the pianist at our favorite restaurant), so a power cord for home use might serve best.
--- Instruction booklet need major overhaul and is not written in well English very good. It also says the battery compartment has a screw, but it does not. So if you're worried about small children, know that the compartment does NOT have hardware. (funny how it warns not to use sharp objects on the keys as it could cause `..fatal..' damage, but I'm quite sure it means permanent product failure and not risk to human life.)
--- Does using something with only 37 keys, ruin someone from ultimately learning properly on a standard piano, or is it a good start ?.?.

product_title: Battlestar Galactica
review_headline: A fun and engaging social game if your gamers know about the series...
review_body:
Battlestar Galactica: The Board Game (BSGBG) is a fun and socially engaging game. For those familiar with BSG, it recreates the first leg of the exodus (post-destruction of the 12 Colonies to New Caprica) (the first expansion takes it beyond that). [For those not familiar with the series, it is about a race of humans fleeing from a \\"race\\" of robots (called Cylons) that humanity originally created but the Cylons decided to turn on them and wipe them out. The remnants of humanity are now fleeing, seeking a new home. The Cylons have infiltrated the remnants with human-looking Cylons in an attempt to make sure the remnant is doomed to extinction.]

How the game plays is that each player plays as one of the main characters from the series. Each character has a series of skills (ex. piloting/engineering/etc.) where he/she gets cards from as well as a special abilities unique to that character. Then each player is dealt a loyalty card which is kept secret (it will say either you are a Cylon or not a Cylon). Then the President of the Colonies as well as the Admiral of the Fleet are determined (based on an order of succession). (The President gets special ability cards via the Quorum deck while the Admiral gets to determine jump location and command of the nuclear weapons about the Battlestar Galactica.) Each player's turn works along these lines:
1) get new skill cards (based on the skills printed on the char. card that he/she is playing)
2) perform an action (ex. fire Galactica's guns, launch fighter, get the ship ready to jump, etc.)
3) draw a crisis card

It is at the crisis cards that tension builds, since almost every crisis card runs along the lines of \\"unless you have skill cards in total value of X (of 1 or more colors), something bad will happen\\". This is where folks will say how many skill cards (which all have a numeric value between 1 and 5) they are contributing to the crisis. Everyone then throws in their cards plus 2 additional ones from a \\"destiny deck\\". The combined deck is shuffled and then flipped over. The skill cards with the colors on the crisis card add positively while any other colors contribute negatively. (ex. A crisis card requires 15 using yellow and green. Well, 7 cards are thrown

product_title: ZeroWater ZJ-003 Filtration Water Cooler Bottle with Electronic Tester, Filters Included
review_headline: Z-Bottle, Convienence is the name of the game
review_body: I've been buying bottled water for years and was kinda getting tired of always hauling the cases of water around. Then my girlfriend talked myself and one of my children into a diet that included drinking a large quantity of water a day, so I decided it was time to switch to the 5-gallon bottles and a dispenser. Found a wonderful stainless dispenser at [...] that makes hot water hot enough for tea and cold water just right for drinking. So now I have to mess with the 5-gallon water bottles. This basically gave me, I thought, 3 options. Having a water delivery service (very expensive), picking up 5-gallon water bottles pre-filled at a place like Home Depot, or taking the empty water bottles in to Wal-Mart and for $2.00 a bottle, refilling them myself. All of these options required that I have storage for a couple empties, and all of them have varying degrees of annoyance. Then while walking through the Home Depot I came across the Z-bottles by ZeroWater. Seemed like the answer to all of my problems.     So, I bought the bottle and hooked it up. Went easily into the new water dispenser and immediately started making water. I personally really like the taste of the water. I have one daughter who belives it tastes metallic, and a couple other household members who really like it. If you think about it, Dasani starts with purified water (000) then adds stuff to it for flavor, so not real surprising that the flavor is not something enjoyed by all, though I myself am real happy. Would be nice if the ZeroWater people could come up with a second type of filter that would add back some stuff to improve that flavor back to a Dasani flavor or something (believe I heard that Dasani measures like 039 parts per million of total disolved solids.     Anyway, for me, this Z-bottle is the way to go. I'm not storing anything but new filters. No huge 5-gallon water bottles sitting around. I'm not lifting and changing water bottles. I'm not running water bottles to the store, or paying acrazy amount of money to have them delivered. All I'm doing is filling a pitcher with water every night and dumping it into the top chamber of the Z-bottle. Nothing could be easier.

product_title: Breville BJS600XL Fountain Crush Masticating Slow Juicer
review_body:
I confess, I balked at this cost for any kitchen appliance that doesn't clean up after itself ;). But it is worth it, every penny. VERY quiet - couldn't believe it! Less pulp, more juice. The manufacturer claims that more soluble fiber is left in the juice, and that the juice can be thicker. I've not noticed a real difference there, but my 12-year-old centrifugal juicer was very low end when I bought way back then. As for ease of clean-up - MUCH easier than my old one. Cleans up quickly, and with all the alignment marks and things fitting into place just so, it is a snap to, clean, to put together and to take apart. Heavy duty, I think it will last me a good long time. With Amazon free shipping on items over $25, I scored.

While it is called a \\"slow\\" juicer because of the \\"chewing\\" action of the screw, it is NOT really \\"slow\\". So if you're serious about juicing vegetables for the long haul - this is a great investment!

(Even with the reduced pulp, I still get enough to make veggie stock afterwards.)

Enjoy, juice on!

product_title: Aroma Arc-3-Cup (Uncooked) 6-Cup (Cooked) Rice Cooker and Food Steamer
review_headline: The little rice cooker that could!
review_body:
I absolutely love this rice cooker. First and foremost, I received this same rice cooker in red as a Christmas gift from my mother last year. However, I felt daunted by it after one use (where I didn't properly read the manual and used far too little water) and it sat in my cupboard, unused, for quite a while until my boyfriend threw it out by accident as he thought it did not work.

On a quest to 1) make healthier dinner choices and 2) find a use for the vegetables that I use for my work lunches before they spoil, I decided to come back to the original rice cooker that I didn't bother tackling before. This time, I chose a different color because white was less expensive than any other color -- which is always great to remember to double-check when you're purchasing on Amazon. At $17, compared to what they sell for in local stores (roughly around $23 at time of writing this), I felt like it was a good deal.

For the beginner to rice cookers, you should always remember that you should take every opportunity to "spice things up a bit" -- that is, go wild with your spices that you add to your water! While it may be silly, I didn't even really think about this -- I had this vision of "vegetables and white rice" in my mind when I saw my rice cooker before. Not true! You can change the spices up so many ways to have very different tasting dishes. You can also add a chicken bouillon cube for extra flavor -- just make sure to stir your rice very well after you've finished cooking!

In regards to steaming vegetables, I often throw an array of vegetables together -- leftover onion, asparagus, cabbage, etc. I also use frozen vegetables. Yes, frozen! I rinse them with hot water under the faucet in a strainer, drain, and transfer to my steaming plate. I've found that they taste just fine in a hurry and, quite honestly, it's a great way to save on grocery costs, too. I would suggest trying it out! I personally like to salt and peppermy vegetables before I put the lid on top, since it will fall down into the rice during the steaming process. Always remember to line the hands up with your rice cooker and

product_title: T-fal EZ Clean Stainless Steel Immersion Deep Fryer
review_headline: The Drain and Oil Container is a Killer Feature
review_body:
Having owned a deep fryer in the past, I really appreciate how the drain and oil container improve cleanup. With my previous deep fryer, I would leave/store the oil in the fryer itself, then change it every 8-10 fry sessions. This meant that I had to spend a significant amount of time/effort scrubbing off the built up and caked on oil on all of the components. With with this Emeril model, I simply flip the drain switch, come back in a few hours once the oil has cooled/drained, then give the basin and heating elements a quick hand wash. Overall, the Emeril model stays much cleaner than my last fryer. Additionally, because the drain has a somewhat dome shape, much of the sediment from the oil tends to remain in the basin after draining, reducing the particulate in your used oil.

Two negatives about this model. First, the display does not tell you the actual temperature of the oil, just the target temperature. Second, it does not allow you to set a custom temperature, you must choose from several predetermined temps. That said, the drain/storage feature more than makes up for these deficiencies.

product_title: Laptop Lunches Bento-Ware Bento Buddies, Made in the USA, Leakproof BPA Free Containers, Use on their own or with the Bento Box
review_headline: A Must-Have for Your Laptop Lunch Kit!
review_body:
I love my Laptop Lunch set, but it is made infinitely more versatile with the addition of a couple of sets of Bento Buddies. The Bento Buddies set contains an extra lidded container in each of the sizes already included with the basic Laptop Lunch sets, as well as a large lidded container that doesn't come as part of the basic set.

I've been using the system for about 18 months now and can definitely say the more containers you have, the better! Always having a few clean ones stacked and waiting in the cupboard while the used ones are in the dishwasher means that I can plan ahead and pack leftovers and snacks when I have the time, making it pretty much effortless when it comes to actually putting a lunch box together in the morning. The large lidded container in particular is invaluable - there are days when I want to pack lots of nibbly little snacks, and days when I just want to cram in a ton of leftover pasta or chili or the previous night's Thai takeout, or possibly a big salad, and on those days, the cute little boxes just don't cut it!

like MXR Chorus, Boss Chorus,TC-Chorus, etc. I find that this Callisto is more a very musical chorus
than other! It is superb sounding, not a overload Chorus (most people don't like), is easy to use.
Sounds very good and has no critical points as other with different amps or guitars!

Though It cost more than some other chorus it is worth every EURO or Dollar!
You will get a deep clear chorus (just like the Providence Anadime Chorus, which cost more) with fine sparkles.
It doesn't get muddy when you push the signal,
The Callisto is very versatile, not too much vibrato. You will get it, you love it.

If you are a critical Musician by effects, I believe you won't regret to buy one.
Catalinbread makes a lot of very useful effects!

review_body: My family recently switched to the SBD lower carb lifestyle with great success. While other reviewers have said this isn't good for low-carb diets, I beg to differ. My family loves pancakes, so I was excited to find this as an option. About once or twice each month I make pancakes with this and they are AWESOME. We always add some cinnamon and sometimes we add mashed bananas or NSA applesauce instead of oil. It's a treat with sugar-free syrup, of course, but it's a far healthier treat than a Bisquick pancake. I have no idea what anyone means about fish or soy taste in the other reviews. Perhaps they aren't seasoning the mix when using it for breading or baking. Even my super picky husband asks me to bake him pancakes with this!

product_title: Honey Pearls, 40 Single Serving Packets, White Lion Tea
review_body: Update 4/9/09:  I never heard back from White Lion through the Amazon email system.  However, a few weeks later I got a promotional email from their marketing dept., so I replied with the same question.  Their response:    \\"The sugar involved in the Honey Pearls process is certified kosher and thus has minimal processing before being introduced to the honey, which is combined in a mechanical process, rather than chemical.\\"    I replied \\"Isn't it a little misleading to advertise them as '100% natural dry honey' if you're adding sugar to the honey?\\", their response:    \\"The sugar and the honey are both natural ingredients. We do plainly list sugar as an ingredient due to the product needing the sugar to allow for the crystallization to occur.\\"    ... but they don't mention sugar on the Amazon description.    Original Post:  A few days after I ordered this product I got a message from Amazon saying that White Lion had not confirmed receipt of the order and Amazon considered the order canceled.  Then a couple days later I received a shipping notice.  So White Lion got the order but didn't bother to communicate back to Amazon.      The product arrived and the ingredients are \\"honey and sugar\\".  I sent an email to While Lion through Amazon three days ago asking \\"Sugar?  As in processed sugar?\\" but I haven't heard back from them.  My trust is waning as the days go by.

product_title: Clif Kid Choc Zbar Brwnie 6pk Org
review_body:
If I had kids, I'd be stealing these out of their lunch bag. Cheeky bastards!

I get afternoon chocolate cravings and can't scarf down Snickers bars everyday (at least not if I'm spending most of my day sedentary in an offic chair). The zBar Brownies offer all the satisfaction of chocolate with the wholesomeness of oatmeal.

Ok, so it's not as rich and creamy as something from Hershey. But they are damn good without olestra, saccharine, and other ingredients that will embalm you. And the #1 ingredient is Organic Oats. The #2 ingredient is organic chocolate chips. If that wasn't a good enough start, all the other ingredients are organic too.

1 bar = 1 serving

120 calories

25 calories from fat

1g of saturated fat

0g trans fat

0mg cholesterol

The biggest downside is 12g of sugar, but that's still doing better than most sweet snacks.

I love these bars because they are tasty and filling. They are a \\"healthy\\" alternative to the tempations in your local vending machine.

Cheers!

product_title: The Spice Lab Halen Mon Pure Welsh Silver Finishing Sea Salt - Isle of Anglesey - Wales  UK, 1-Count Packages (Pack of 3)
review_body: I disagree with the previous reviewer. I paid $14 for one of the bigger jars of the Victoria brand salt and vowed to never buy another finishing salt again. It's sweet, light, and perfect for sprinkling without fear of overkill. This salt tastes like regular $5 salt to me. I'd send it back if it wouldn't cost nearly as much to ship it, but trust me when I tell you the Victoria brand is unlike anything you've ever tasted. I read the backs of both jars and this one is harvested from the whole island, where the Victoria brand is harvested from the one coast. Don't know if it makes a difference, but the sodium content is much higher in this brand and therefore a little too twingy for my taste.

product_title: Kong Air Squeaker Tennis Balls
review_body:
My gentle Golden who's not yet out of the puppy stage (but is 7 months old) loves this ball.
There's a couple of health issues, however, that make it impossible to live with.
A) The \\"fur\\" tuft that covers the ball is easily shedded and ingestible. Whatever it is, probably is bad for the dog and I can't keep her from tearing off the furry part. It sheds without much trying.
B) The entire outer part comes off. It's just glued onto a squeaky ball. That's all lit is. My dog was eating the stuff off when I noticed about an inch gone and then I was able to (without effort) just peel away the entire section (half the ball). I came here to post some photos of it but see others have already done it so no need.
Lastly, there's a little plastic \\"button\\" on one end that would eventually get eaten and has a prong inside of it.
This toy isn't safe.
It's fun, but not safe.
My dog isn't a hugh chewer, likes the softer squeaky toys and hasn't destroyed things she's had since she was only 6 lbs. I think it's called a \\"soft mouth\\". She just takes care of many beloved things. Stuffed animal toys, softer kong things, etc.
So I'd think twice about this particular item. It just needs some tweaking to be safe. It's a wonderful idea because unlike regular tennis balls it squeaks without too much effort. Hope this helps.

review_body: This is a whole lot more affordable than a conventional fence.  I found it easy to set up also.  This web site  does not let you down. PetSafe wanted the item returned and would review the return within 48 hours of receiving it....how am I keeping the dog in the yard while I wait for the review?! Not so funny how a company that sells pet products and is called PetSafe cares much less than Amazon about replacing a defective product like the in-ground fence. That's why I buy from this sight. In less than 60 days it has stopped working. The open loop signal started going off even when I cut a short piece of wire to test the transmitter to make sure the buried wire was not broken. review_body: I was extremely disappointed in the door design, workmanship and overall quality of this crate.  More so because I have owned Midwest Ultima crates since 1998.  My previous crates from this company were well-made, strong, sturdy, and the two I have are still going strong.  I needed another 42-inch crate for my car to transport my new dog, and was initially very happy that I could get one for a less expensive price than I had previously paid.  But that should have been the warning sign.  The crate was flimsy, did not open easily without catching on other parts of the crate; the doors did not open and close smoothly - I had to giggle the doors to get them to line up with the slide latches & openings.  The crate handle was missing, although I doubt it would have been useful.  I am returning the crate for a refund and will shop around for something of better quality.  Even if I have to pay more.  To Midwest Homes for Pets... this was a huge disappointment.  Please revive your old methods of manufacturing these crates, and make them like you used to.

The bed part is so cushy and inviting, I couldn't help but stick my head in there! The cover is stiff enough to provide an envelope for your pet to crawl into, but it folds around them nicely, like a thick blankie.
It is machine washable, a definate plus! The color is similar to the picture: kind of a cadet blue with a subtle stripe pattern, and the inside is cream colored. My pup had NO reservations about heading in there! I tossed a toy in it and she ran right in! She's in there as I type this, poking her nose out every so often to say \\"THANKSMOM!\\"
A great buy for chilly pets--now if they could only make one in MY size!

product_title: Char-Griller Square Inch Charcoal Grill / Smoker
review_body:
Perfect Grill. I have had this grill for 2 years now. It stays outside, with the fitted cover. Yes it has rust were the coal tray is, which is to be excepted as much as I use it.

Couple of cons.
The front wooden tray has very week metal supports. Very flimsy design. The side wooden tray metal support are a better design but not good enough to support the grills weight when moving it. Lastly. The wheels, its a grill they always suck.

Pros.
Thick gauge steel design has proven to stand up. Tubular housing construction is a major plus. This grill is sturdy and solid because of it. The cast Iron grates are freakin awesome.

This is a great grill to own. Some advice from me. Buy a spray bottle. put about 4 ounces of olive oil, 20 or so ounces of any other cheaper oil and top with water. Shake to mix. Spay the outside of grill, inside of grill and grates. This will season it and help protect the grill. I do this every so often maybe once every three or four months. I use this mixture on the grates every time I cook to help keep the grates non-stick, and flavored.

Remember this grill is metal, it will mostly likely sit outside or in your garage. Some parts will rust, None have evn came close to rusting through the metal. Know how to take care of your grill. If you just want to use it once or twice a year, then maybe you should just go to the dollar store and but a 10 or 20 dollar model there every year.

product_title: Cohas Chalkboard Labels in Oval Shape for 8 and 12 Ounce Quilted Crystal Jelly Jars comes with or without Liquid Chalk Marker
review_body:
I bought these labels to use for canning in order to have a reusable label. These were advertised as dishwasher safe. Well, sometimes they are, and sometimes they aren't. I've had numerous ones come off in the dishwasher while others stay firmly attached. The ones that do survive the dishwasher usually do not survive a second canning process, so they have limited use for canners.

The other thing I didn't like about them is that even after the chalk dries, it is way too easy to wipe off the lettering just by casually touching it. I never had to use glass cleaner to remove the chalk. I just looked at them and they practically wiped clean.

Overall, I think the labels are decent enough but not terribly practical for canning purposes--which they are advertised for. I will go back to the labels that dissolve next year.

product_title: Planet Bike Cascadia Front and Rear Bicycle Fender Set with Mud Flaps
review_body: UPDATE: May 1, not quite five months since I finally managed to install these fenders, the front fender failed. I was making a slow turn into a bike lane when I experienced the much dreaded toe overlap - where the rider's foot interferes with the front wheel.  This isn't uncommon with small framed bikes that have large 700c wheels but it's usually more of an annoyance than anything else.     Maybe it was the pressure from my foot on the thin plastic that caused the front fender to fold under itself which resulted in the bike coming to an abrupt stop, causing me to fall. I can only be thankful that it happened in a buffered bike lane rather than in traffic, and that I only sustained a sprained wrist. I'll be removing these fenders as soon as I regain use of my left hand.    ==============  Original Review    Its been two days since the fenders arrived and I began trying to install them on my '04 Sirrus. I had previously used [[ASIN:B002KCFSPI Planet Bike Hardcore Road Fender]] so I presumed these would be similar.   Right out of the box I noticed they appeared quite slim and although they're recommended for tires up to 700x28 they're a close fit on my Armadillos 700x25.    The 42m bolt supplied was a bit too short for my Specialized Sirrus fork so I would up using the old bolt that originally came with the Hardcore Fenders.  The plastic clip that secures the rear fender to the brake bridge was a press fit on my old Hardcore fenders and held the the fender firmly in place. On the Cascadia the same bracket has a loose fit and will slide up and down the fender. More importantly these fenders lack the metal tab that hooks onto the chainstay connector and helps keep the bottom portion of the rear fender in place.     Like others have mentioned, I also had a bolt in the chainstay connector so I cut a slit to slide the fender over the bolt. What I didn't anticipate is there's very little clearance with the front Nexave Derailleur. As a result the fender is pushed back and winds up rubbing against the rear tire. While this worked perfectly well with the old Hardcore fenders,

product_title: Razor RipRider 360 Caster Trike
review_body:
Putting this together Christmas Eve, my husband wondered if my 7 year old son would really have any interest in it. He thought is was too much like a big wheel and would be boring for him. Christmas morning comes and son seems excited about it but really has no clue as to what will happen when he rides it.

Later that morning, son and husband go outside to ride and son comes running back in the house, face flushed, laughing hysterically - he had no idea it would turn on a dime and he absolutely loved it. Kid from down the street came over and he tried it and hated it! He said he would never ride it again because he was afraid of it...I see this as a good thing!

I do wish the seat were adjustable because my son is very tall for his age and I don't know how long he will be able to ride but it really is a lot of fun and is a good quality product.

product_title: Camp Chef Triton 10L Portable Water Heater
review_headline: Great product. Easy to install and use
review_body: Great product. Easy to install and use. It gives you continuous hot water on demand. I highly recommend purchasing the Triton 10L.

product_title: Pearl iZUMi Attack Low Sock 3-Pack
review_body: I picked these up because my previous pair of Pearl iZUMi low socks were pretty decent socks. That was a few years ago, the ones I ordered most recently were super thin - we're talking thin dress sock thin - and they also seemed quite a bit bigger than the previous pair. My heel slips out of my cycling shoe with these socks. I'd highly recommend getting a bit thicker or nicer pair of socks, even for hot weather.

product_title: High Sierra AT3 Drop-Bottom Wheeled Duffle
review_body: I bought this bag for a 3 week trip to Patagonia and it far exceeded my expectations.  On past trips I carried two conventional wheeled bags and wanted one bag for all my travel needs but still be able to stay within the 50 pound limit.  I was totally amazed by how roomy this duffle is and yet still relatively lightweight, weighing just under 11 pounds.  Yet it is extreemly well constructed and rugged.  I took a total of 6 flights on the trip and there is no evidence of any wear at all, although in fairness there should be no wear at this point.  The big thing I liked is the separate zipped compartment in the bottom of the bag where it holds a LOT of clothing and other gear.  The top compartment is great for shoes, rain gear, sweaters and anything you don't mind getting a bit wrinkled.  There are three other zipped compartments also which come in handy for misc items.  It is very easy to stay well organized with this duffle!!!  The bottom line is I got everything I needed to take on this trip in this one bag and still came in at 47 pounds, which amazed me.  The wheels roll very easily and are designed into the bag somewhat which should reduce the potential for getting broken when being tossed around.  Another big plus is the top handle which makes it much easier to handle the bag and load in/out of car trunks or van storage space.  I highly recommend this duffle - it is far superior to any other I researched and I spent a lot of time reviewing various rolling duffles.

product_title: Frogg Toggs Women's All Purpose Suit
review_body: I have used every device and piece of clothing for rainwear known to man. Frogg Toggs are simply the best and are unbeatable. This is a set for my wife, so she'll stop taking mine. The typical raincoat, rainsuit, poncho, and garbage bag stop the rain by sealing you in an unbreathable sweat machine. I've used these on cold football sidelines and tropical Mexican jungles. Always comfortable, worth every penny and actually work.

product_title: Yaktrax Run Traction Cleats for Running on Snow and Ice
review_body: Just got them in the mail and took them out for a 14 mile run on ice and packed snow. Worked perfect. I didn't slip once. They were easy on and off my sneakers. Definetly worth it if you want to run during the bad weather of winter.

product_title: Timbuk2 Freestyle Bag
review_body:
Bought this with traveling with my iPad in mind. There's simply no way yours won't be kept safe and secure here. I opted to take scissors to the sewn-in dedicated case and then I handed that piece of finery over to a friend whose iPad has been going naked. I did this partly because my iPad case is already substantial and because this freed up space inside the bag.

You couldn't ask for a better, more thoughtful piece of engineering. It's as if someone at Timbuk2 followed me around and studied my needs. All sorts of cool pockets, secure and just the right size. But not too many.

My only complaint is that the velcro is just a bit too strong--and it loves catching hold of my clothing when not secured. A small price to pay for something that is as cute and perfect as this sweet bag.

review_body: I bought this stove a few weeks ago for a backpacking trip in the California Sierras. We used the stove twice a day and it worked great (one match to light every time even in windy conditions). The stove is unbelievably light and fits in a tiny sack which can easily be stored inside pots and pans for protection. It is also surprisingly stable considering its' size. The manual says the stove is compatible only with Coleman propane/butane canisters but it will work with any propane/butane canister. I used the MSR brand. I used one 4 oz. cannister in four days (7 meals plus boiling water for tea, hot chocolate). In summary, this is a great product for a great price. Similar stoves I looked at were heavier and twice the price.

product_title: Bicycles Motobike Safety Spiral Cable Combination Lock Black Blue
review_body:
Item came with no instructions on how to open lock and change combination. I was totally unfamiliar with this type of lock and it took me a long time to figure it out. Here are the instructions:
1. Set the lock to 0000 to open it.
2. Keeping the numbers at 0000, turn the wheel on the outside clockwise and hold it there. You may need a pair of pliers to turn that wheel. With the black wheel in the clockwise position, rotate each dial to the desired combination and then rotate the black wheel counterclockwise to its original position.

The cable is very thick and plastic coated. It should be tough to break into.

product_title: Kodak HERO 6.1 Wireless Color Printer with Scanner, Copier & Fax
review_body:
I have been a Canon or HP user for printers for over 20 years. My last printer was a Canon and it broke down after just a year and to say the least I was very disappointed with it. So I thought I would look for another printer. I went to various magazines and on-line reviews and they this printer very good standing. I decideded to purchase one and I love it. All the controls are in the front and in an order that make sense. Also, it found my Wi-Fi network all on it own. My wife's new laptop found it and installed all the necessary drivers and she now prints her stuff from the living room where she does most of her work. She has all the features of the printer as I do.

The setup was very simple and it took me about 10-15 minutes to do the entire setup. It also went on the internet to get new updates of software and firmware. I suggested this printer to a neighbor and I let him have temporary access to my network and he was able to print a 20 page report, which included charts and images. He lived 2 doors down and across the hall and he had no problems with the printout, he used the auto duplex and he was shocked at the crispness of the report. He also sent a fax to my printer using an older fax machine and I handed it to him and the fax was just great.

He decided to order one and he was going to order the large cartridges and I told him not to, because Kodak included the large cartridges. Also I told him the cost of the cartridges and he could not believe [[ASIN:B005K8AV2Y Kodak HERO 6.1 Wireless Color Printer with Scanner, Copier & Fax]] how cheap they are.

I have also printed out some images of mine that included images I had taken through my telescope and they came out wonderful. They came out so wonderful, I sent a set to my mother, who has a sight problem, and she could see the images so well, she could make out what the images so well, she could tell what objects they were.

I recommend this printer for anyone

product_title: The Pencil Grip Writing CLAW for Pencils and Utensils, Medium Size, 6 Count Blue/Red (TPG-21206)
review_headline: Turns out my kid doesn't see the world in scribbles :)
review_body: This pencil grip is amazing! I have a 5 year old and a 4 year old and my 5 year old has been writing fine since he was 3, so when my 4 year old continued to draw scribbles and have no interest in forming letters I thought it might be a grip issue. I bought those triangle crayons and then triangle colored pencils and nothing changed. Therefore i concluded that the traditional triangle pencil grip would not help much either. I bought this one because I saw someone posted a that it was great for their child with cerebral palsy. My child doesn't have that but if helped the other kid then it stands to reason it could help my kid. As soon as the grip came I helped my son put his fingers in and I kid you not he wrote his name and a bunch of very detailed stick people. It was like he understood how but his little hands just weren't fine tuned enough to do it for him. I'm sure developmentally he would have eventually got the fine motor skills down, but why not give him something to help him get there quicker? It might not be such a miracle grip for everybody but for the price, I'd sure try it before I let a teacher label my kid as "special" because he only draws scribbles. Just sayin' :)

product_title: Panasonic DECT 6.0 Corded/Cordless Phone with Answering System, Metallic Gray
review_body:
This is a very nice phone with good reception, sound, battery life, features etc. I do recommend it. I will not get into all the positive details because all this review is to point out a couple of cons and I want to keep this simple. There are many very good detailed reviews talking about all the pros already so no point in restating them. There are two cons and I wish I knew about then before I purchased the phone, and did not read about this information in the reviews.

CONS:

1. First, there is no audible sound letting you know you have messages, something I thought was standard on all answer phones these days. But you can program the phones to have a small blinking light when there are unread messages through the code system so not too bad.

2. This is my biggest con, and I cannot figure out why phones have to be so complicated. You would need a small college course to learn everything. There are 47 pages of detailed instructions on how to use all the features. You should be able to navigate to a function using an intuitive menu, not having to look everything up in a book. One example that I could NOT find this in the instructions is that when someone calls you but does not leave a message, you get the words \\"Missed Call\\" on the phones' displays. There is no easy way to delete this so basically your phone will always say \\"Missed Call\\" and you will always wonder was this an old call or a new call. Here is the 9+ step solution to delete it from your display:

a. Hit the \\"Menu\\" button
b. Hit the \\"#\\" button
c. Look up code in book (it is 213)
d. Type in \\"213\\"
e. Hit \\"Scroll List\\"
f. Find phone number to delete
g. Hit \\"Erase\\" button
h. Scroll to \\"Yes\\"
i. Hit \\"Select\\"
j. Now, if you received 10 calls, do this 9 more times

3. There are two pages of codes for you to use to program with. I doubt you will memorize them so you will need to keep the instruction book out for reference.

4. Even with 47 pages, not all the information is in the manual,

review_body: Bought this on the basis of overall positive reviews on amazon. Saw a few negative reports, but was certain it wouldn't be my experience! Worked with three different (overseas) customer service reps over a five hour period. One hung up on me when we were making no progress, the other did not call me back as she said she would, and the third was actually quite helpful ... so much so that I had an internet signal for about 12 hours. And then it died and did not come back. Wife's home office was down, kid's xbox live xmas present was a dud, a day of work down the drain, and I frankly didn't have the endurance to deal with a new batch of customer service people - packed it back up and returned to amazon (the easiest part of this transaction!).

product_title: Kindle Paperwhite, 6" High Resolution Display with Next-Gen Built-in Light, Wi-Fi
review_headline: Terrible battery life and Amazon response
review_body:
The Kindle Paperwhite is great when it works but battery charging is very annoying.

I rarely write negative reviews but I am frustrated by the battery life on my new Kindle Paperwhite. After fully charging it, the charge lasted for less than a week. I called Amazon and was transferred to a Kindle "specialist" in the Philippines who said that the issue was leaving wifi on all the time even though that was never an issue with my Kindle keyboard reader.
I fully charged the Paperwhite again and only turned on the wifi for a few seconds a day to update the Paperwhite. Again after less than a week, the battery was at close to zero charge. I then called again and when I got a "specialist" in the Philippines who was very slow in understanding the issue, I asked to be transferred to a US Kindle "specialist".
She told me that my brand new Kindle was several software versions behind and that the only way to update it was to manually download and install the latest updates which she assured me would fix the problem.

After another week, the battery is again near zero charge despite updating the software and turning off wifi 99.9% of the time.
I am about to waste time yet again with Kindle support when the issue is obviously a faulty battery.

The Kindle Paperwhite charge is listed as keeping a charge for up to 8 weeks and only needs to be charged on a monthly not weekly basis. ?????

product_title: ASUS TF201 Transformer
review_body: This is the first review I have written, and I wish it was because I was thrilled with my purchase. Unfortunately this is not the case. After charging my ASUS Transformer Prime for 8 hours, I powered it up.  It went directly to set-up.  After selecting the language, the screen read, WiFi connecting.  It never went beyond that spot.  After reading a few forums, I found out that this has been an ongoing problem with this tablet.  The forums suggested a factory re-boot.  I decided to return the product.  I noticed on closer inspection a few sign of previous use.  Fingerprints on the back of the tablet and a smudge on the screen.  I am not sure it was a new tablet.  I did package everything up to return to Amazon, printed a label and shipped back the tablet. I called before returning the package and talked to customer service.  They were great and the agent even offered to send me an e-mail when the package was delivered to Amazon.I have to say that I buy almost exclusively from Amazon and I have only returned one other purchase due to the wrong item being shipped. I feel that this is a problem with ASUS, not Amazon.

product_title: Iomega  Home Media 1 TB Network Attached Storage 34337
review_headline: Poof, all my files disappeared and Iomega is no help
review_body: I've had this drive for over a year and I've had 3 major problems.  Most recently all my files disappeared, and the drive is showing that it's empty.  This just happened overnight.  Iomega is not at all helpful.  Indeed, if you try to post a comment on Iomega's website asking for recovery help (nothing nasty just for help), Iomega moderators will not post it.  The drive cannot be counted upon for reliable backup.  Shortly after I got the drive, half of its capacity just disappeared and Iomega's only advice was to reformat the drive.  My last problem with this drive is that even though it purports to be gigabit, it's incredibly slow to read or write to -- what's the point of having gigabit ethernet if the drive itself can't read or write files at more than 1% of that speed?  It's painfully slow for computer backups and has trouble sending video files over a hardwired connection to my router (and then hardwired to the TV).

product_title: Kingston ValueRAM 800MHz DDR2 Desktop Memory
review_headline: Kingston Memory, the Honda Civic of RAM.
review_body:
IT'S RAM! AAAWWWWWWW YIS!!! RAAAAAAMMMMMMM!!!!!!!

Works fine, sticks are very small compared to other memory modules, like half the height. Also, it's Kingston so you know it's going to work in a majority of systems. Kingston Memory, the Honda Civic of RAM. Can't believe how cheap it is too, even at this age, or maybe despite of it's age. Works fine in dual channel too (no idea why matching chips wouldn't, but I thought I'd add that).

Anyway, it's working great, though I did have to set my memory frequency manually in the bios to keep the rig from BSODing (stupid motherboard issue, NOT the ram) Please note this stuff did NOT like to run clean at slower settings, which is hardly uncommon, though some of the higher quality (the turbo racing stuff with neon and heat sinks on it) has a broader tolerance for motherboard Auto setting idiocy.

Anyway, for the price, this is awesome. Would get this for any clients PC that needed an upgrade or a repair.

product_title: BolseÂ® 300Mbps Wireless-N mini Router / AP / Repeater (802.11 b/g/n) Wireless Amplifier, Including LAN Connection, WPS button
review_headline: Won't setup, can you help..if not returning!!!!
review_body:
Ok first off I'm not a novice at setting up network devices nor a newbie to this stuff, but this thing is about to go in the garbage!

We purchased this because my husband won a blu-ray with streaming capabilities from work and it's not wireless, so we thought from the description and such that this adapter would work to hard-wire the blu-ray to our wireless network without running 80ft of cable from one end of the house to the other end and upstairs. Well it has been useless so far!

I have no idea what is wrong but I cannot get this thing to setup. I'm running Windows 8, ( have tried on a 2 other computers as well Windows 7 and Vista) I see the router (Wireless N) in available connections, I click on it. The software asks me for the router pin (we have a belkin router) I enter it, then enter the network name I'm using and the password..then the stupid thing says my router pin is wrong (it is not wrong!, logged into router to check it and then I entered it correctly about 30 times, then changed the pin and enter new pin another 30 times..it's not me enter the incorrect pin). This occurred on all 3 computers, each running a different Windows operating system.

There is no support page online and no customer service numbers so if anyone has any ideas, I would much appreciate it. I will check this for about week..no responses and this damn this is going back!

review_headline: Very nice cover, after adding duct tape.
review_body: This kindle HD 7", 3rd generation cover has pluses and minuses. First, it is very nicely made and is an exacting fit, and that is where the problem comes in. It fits so snugly that the power button on the cover hits the power button on the kindle and it starts turning the kindle off. The fix is to put a small piece of duct tape on the cover by the power button so that it creates just enough space to prevent the cover button from turning it off. Yeah, duct tape saves the day again.  You also have to view the photos that came with the cover carefully of how to fold it. If you fold it out, it doesn't work as well because the magnets won't keep it folded. Once you get past these two hurdles, you're set.

review_headline: Problem with Dell Optiplex GX 620  (Mfg date 03-2006)
review_body: This switch does not work for two of my machines at work (both are Dell Optiplex GX 620, Mfg date 03-2006).    The switch drops key strokes frequently and sometimes a key stroke is repeated several times when typing.  If the active machine is left idle for a while, both keynoard and mouse will be lost.  One has to hit [ScrLk] [ScrLk] [Enter] to switch to other machine and swithc back to re-establish connectivity.    The keyboard used in this case is Microsoft Natural 4000 and Optical Mouse 5000.    Contacted the IOGEAR tech support, and the representitive acknowledged that this is a known problem with Dell Optiplex GX 620s (due to the chipsets on motherboard).    Returned the item and bought a MiniView 4-port (GCS1774), which works wonderfully.

review_body:
This is an updated review:
I've changed my rating from 1 star to 4 stars because The Warming Company replaced the fan within a week and the new fan has been running fine ever since. It is now January and so far no problems. I run it plugged in but have tested it with batteries also.

Although I did not purchase this through Amazon I wanted to leave a review so buyers can beware. I bought this fan about 6 weeks ago from The Warming Store and it has already stopped working properly. The low setting still works but it goes slower than it did originally. The high setting turns on for about 2 seconds and then stops. It will keep trying to start but then jerks and/or only spins once and stops again. The high setting is completely useless now. I see others have had the same issue. Maybe we all got a defective batch. I've contacted The Warming Store about a replacement and I'll report back on how they handled the issue.

product_title: Werner (MT) Telescoping Multiladder
review_body:
I feel profoundly uncomfortable while on a ladder and my husband has a problem with heights, so when we sold our two story house last year we also sold our extension ladder. Our plan was to buy a one story home and never again need to be high up on a ladder. Well, we found our one story home, but quickly realized our current 12 foot telescoping ladder wouldn't reach most of the exterior (or interior heights.) Since I would be the one getting on the ladder, above all else I wanted stability. The ability to store the ladder in a small space was also high on our list of requirements because as homeowners, we will only need to use the ladder a few times a year.

This weekend we tried out the ladder. We had minor repair work that was needed on our stucco due to chipping from a recent hail storm. The damage was at various heights and on three sides of the house. We knew we could handle the job, the problem was being able to reach all the areas that needed a touch-up. Additionally, there are significant grading issues around the perimeter of the home to contend with so the ladder needs to be quite flexible in its positions. This ladder enabled us to make short work out of a small but tedious task, and permitted us to reach around windows and downspouts while in its extension ladder configuration.

We own a cosco 12 foot telescoping ladder, so we were definitely comparing the Werner ease of use with that ladder. The position changes were accomplished much easier and with greater efficiency with the Werner. I also felt more stable on the Werner ladder even though both our cosco and Werner ladders flare out at the bottom for greater stability. The only difficulty we encountered was in using the highest position of the extension ladder. The cosco is smaller and thus more manageable. It would have been helpful to have read the reviews before trying out the full extension because another reviewer's suggestion of extending the bottom half of the ladder and then leaning the ladder against the house while raising up the top portion would have been more safer and easier. We ended up laying the ladder on the ground and each taking an end, which is also how we released the extension -

product_title: 4 Pairs of Harn Clip-On Drawer Brackets
review_headline: Easy fix for my broken drawer!!!
review_body:
A couple weeks ago one of the drawer brackets of my metal sided harn drawer broke. These brackets allowed me to easily fix the drawer in around 10 minutes. They did not come with any instructions, but it was pretty easy to figure out how to use them.

Here are the steps I took:

1. First I traced around the old brackets with pencil, so I would know where the new brackets should be placed.
2. Unlatched the bracket that wasn't broken by inserting a phillips screw driver in the hole above the spring and depressing the spring while simultaneously pulling the metal drawer side out of the bracket.
3. Removed the old drawer brackets and replaced them with the new brackets.
4. Inserted the metal drawer sides into the brackets and pushed until the brackets clicked and the springs were exposed.

product_title: Waste King Legend Series 1/2 HP Continuous Feed Garbage Disposal with Power Cord - (L-2600)
review_body: Bought to replace an InSinkErator Badger5+ (5/8hp) that had begun to leak after 10+ years of excellent service.  The pricing on Badgers had gone up over the past decade, so I looked elsewhere and found the Waste King.  Good price, good ratings, so I took a chance.    So far, so good.  The motor sounds a lot different compared to the Badger, but it works fine.    If you're at all handy, the installation of the actual unit is pretty easy.  But I do have a few pointers.    1.  Make sure the rubber cushion mount ring is seated properly on the sink flange.  Just the top lip of that rubber ring should seat in the channel of the flange.  It is easy to seat the rubber ring too high, one notch up, so to speak.  It looks right, it feels right, but it's not right.  If it's too high up the flange, it won't let the metal mount ring slide down enough.  You'll lift up the disposer and there won't be enough clearance for the bayonet-mount (those nubs)on the disposer unit to mate with the mount ring. Pretty frustrating at the time.  But once I found my mistake, it was easy to hang the disposer.    2.  Go ahead and put some soft soap on the bottom of that rubber ring before you hang the disposer.  I didn't, and it took a bit of effort to get that mount ring turned fully.  A little soft soap should make it slide more easily, and the less you torque on everything down there, the better.      Other than that, it was a piece of cake.  As mentioned, it comes ready to plug into an outlet.  If you don't have an outlet, you'll have to add one, or wire hardwire the unit using the included directions.

That is how smooth it gets it. My other two planers are not even close to this one. Yes it is a little loud, but most of them are. The thing weighs almost 600 lbs. With the cast iron rollers it moves like it weighed hardly anything. I have yet had to sharpen the blades on it. like I said above I run mostly hard wood thru it. I would say I have run almost 1500 board feet thru it with no problems at all. The only thing that I wish it would of come with is a helical head on it. product_title: Dr. Katz TheraBreath PerioTherapy Healthy Gums Toothpaste, 3.5oz
review_body: Using this product for about a month, I noticed a sharp increase in tartar formation. I had been to the dentist in less than 5 months for a cleaning and I floss and brush every day, yet my teeth had patches of tartar that seemed to come overnight and my lower gums ached.  At first I didn't connect the symptoms with this product, but while searching for solutions for the tartar problem and considering a product called Periogen, I came across Amazon reviewer comments discussing the possibility that some oral antibacterial products, by destroying good bacteria as well as bad, may somehow lead to more tartar growth. Periogen, apparently, is not in that category, and I plan to try it as a tartar dis-solver.  I don't know for sure if Katz Perio gel really caused the problem, but it seems a strong possibility since I made no other changes. I decided to go back to Tom's of Maine, which I've used for years. I wanted to give this warning in case someone else experiences the trouble I had with Katz.  I should also mention that in the years before I had begun using Tom's of Maine, I always did have excessive tartar formation, so I must be prone to it, but nothing on the level of what happened almost overnight when using the Katz gel.

review_headline: While the trimming function worked fine the operation of the unit failed after only a ...

Eventually the entire device went dead and it no longer is functional.  For the low price I can't complain but it certainly did not live up to the numerous 5 star reviews. product_title: Cathy Doll Karmart L-glutathione Magic Cream Whitening Pore Tightening Uv A/b/c Made in Korea
review_body: I purchased Cathy Doll about a year ago and still have the giant bottle half full. First of all its freaking sun screen and nothing more. It will not make your skin lighter over the course of using it. When you apply it it has a strong floral fragrance which is nice but when you apply it its just like normal sun screen. Its super runny so do not squeeze the bottle too much because it will all run out of the bottle. So be careful. It leaves a white cast on you and if you are darker it will just look gray and ashy. Its just korean sun screen that says whitening because of the supposed "glutathione" in it. However, glutathione is proven to not change your skin if used topically on the skin. It is probably called whitening sunscreen because it makes you look white or "pastey" when you initially apply it. It is water proof but when you scrub it off your back to your normal self. I do however, like it as a normal everyday sun block on my face. So its okay...

product_title: Boots No7 Protect & Perfect Beauty Serum 1 fl oz (30 ml)
review_body: I really like the Boots No7 product line and I particularly love this serum. From the first time I put in on my face, my face felt good. It made my skin feel soft and healthy after only a few times of using it. I must state here for this review that I have really good skin and a good complexion to begin with - and I want to maintain it which is why I wanted to try this product line. I've done a lot of experimenting and have yet to find anything that I love enough to stick with. However, this may just be the product line for me. I think that it is important to accurately pick the products within the Boots line that are for your skin type. For example, I have dry skin so I would never think of using anything other than formulas that are for dry, mature skin. I want to keep my skin looking good and healthy. I use this product with the day and night cream and I love the face wash (cream). My husband has noticed that my make up looks smoother and better when applied and I attribute this to the new Boots products that I'm using. Thus far, I'm very happy with this brand.

product_title: Easy Spirit Women's Everything Loafer
review_headline: Superior to "all-weather" moc; comfy; 3rd pair I've ordered
review_body: Other companies' keep ruining their mocs for "all weather" with restyling that make their shoes: harder to get on, or unfriendly to orthotics, or less weather-worthy.  Everything from Easy Spirit is superior to those now-failed shoe redesigns.  Sole is very grippy on urban/suburban walkways and driveways in fall, winter and spring precipitation.  VERY easy to slip into. Initially feared it was too open for winter wear, but in my experience decent midweight-to-heavy socks carry you through Jan.-Feb.-Mar. in upper midwest without cold feet.  (If you plow through deep snow you will need a boot of course.)  I've sprayed my Everything shoes with waterproofing and the suede takes it beautifully; first spray in Sept.-Oct. and then reapply later winter to make it through puddles of Mar.=Apr.  Brown still looks velvety after two Wisconsin winters; khaki/tan/taupe held up well too.  Oct. 2014 ordered nice neutral dark green for color variety.  The Everything was harder to find in my size this autumn, otherwise still pleased with quality of manufacture.  "Everyday" is a similar shoe with faux fur (alas I didn't like center seam on top of foot) and 1 or more Easy Spirit clogs appear to have the same great-gripping outsole if you like that Everything feature in a backless style.

product_title: Baggallini Criss Cross Bagg
review_body:
I love this purse enough to buy one in a second color. It is fairly small but holds a lot. It is true, as another reviewer noted, that the middle section does not stay closed, but I use it for things that I want to grab quickly but are not costly should they fall out. I'll describe what I carry moving from the small zipper section in front and moving backward.
Here is what I routinely carry:
In the small front zipper section, I put in a lipstick, small mirror and my cell phone, which is a fold over
In the next zipper section behind this pocket, I use the center zipper section of it for currency and change, the four credit card slots for at least six cards, my license and health care cards. The remainder, I put in the convenient little zipper pocket in there. I also put in a folding hair brush, and a few pens.
In the next large section includes my appointment book, check book and sometimes my digital camera. It would also hold a kindle. A regular water bottle would fit but the section may not zip completely but that would depend on how it is positioned.
The middle section,holds hand sanitizer, mints, hanky, shopping lists, coupons and sometimes my keys although I usually clip them on the handle.
Second larger section holds treats for my small breed service dog, a small wallet with her Service Dog IDs and a folding water bowl. Sometimes I include an 8oz bottle of water.
There is an open pocket in the back that I usually don't use because I simply don't carry much else, but I might put in a church bulletin or something of that kind.
Like all baggallinis, it washes beautifully and seems more than durable. I would certainly recommend it to those who like a smaller bag but can't quite do with the triple zip.

product_title: Kaenon Jetty Polarized Sunglasses
review_headline: Very nice shades at a moderate price, but quality is a little iffy.
review_body:
I have two pairs. I picked up a black pair here, when they were having the summer sale and I got it with the 20% discount, which was a killer deal.

As far as the quality of the glasses go. I agree with Mark Twain \\"Chris\\" review. The lenses, through time, have definitely been harder to clean due to the oily build up from my eyes, sweat, eyeglass cleaner, etc. There is now a smudgy haze, throughout the inside lenses, that doesn't seem to want to come off. Granted, I've had my original glasses (Seaweed) for about two years, but still.

Also, about 3 months into having my original glasses. One of the lenses popped out. Kaenon replaced them for me, free of charge, but that was kind of a bummer, since I bought them originally for $250 + tax. They still aren't right. Every time I clean it (wipe it down), the lenses creak and feel like they are about to pop out.

Overall, I would recommend these glasses because they do look good without looking too huge on your face. I am just a little sketchy about the quality.

product_title: Danner Men's Crater Rim 6" GTX Hiking Boot
review_headline: I was dumbfounded by how comfortable these boots are.
review_body:
I didn't have high expectations. I've spent $250 on boots before, some Oboz that are some sick backpacking boots but as soon as my feet swell up, it's game over and the pain (and golf ball sized blisters) begin. This is on a 6 mile FLAT trail too. So I thought the Danners would be a small upgrade, but not night & day. My requirements were simple... I needed something that could handle a heavy pack in remote areas, handle my high arches gracefully, and not give me unbearable blisters. Met and exceeded with these boots.

I've done 6 miles in the Danners, blister free! With the heavy pack on! I was surprised at how comfy the original insoles are, but I put in my Superfeet shortly after and they're even more comfortable and personalized.

These are burly, heavy boots. The weight is hardly bothersome in my opinion, but something to note. If you're reading this, you're likely not in need of casual boots but in something that will perform very well. These boots deliver and justify their own price. You can't get new shoes in the middle of a hike when the blisters get bad. Just order these now. Amazon's price is very good compared to everywhere else.

Note on the images, the leather on the boot is much more pretty than that awful product pic makes it look. Google images for the boots instead of trusting these!

- - - - -

July 2015 Update, post-Nepal travels

These boots were one of the best investments I made towards my trip. 6/5 stars. I highly recommend them.

I don't have issues with the higher heal that others have mentioned, but I definitely notice the MUCH smaller toe box. Running in these shoes makes the top and arches of my feet cramp with shooting pains after runs over a few miles. They are simply too narrow for my (normal width) feet.

review_body:
Update 6/5/13:
I started running out of battery quickly, and could not figure out why. Well, I now know the problem(s). I turned everything on. If you turn on every bit of technology this phone has to offer, you'll go through the battery faster than a Ferrari goes through gas. I would run out of charge in 14 hours....with very little use. I am now trying to figure out what I can't live without. I still think I have a lot to learn on this phone, especially having discovered \\"developer mode.\\" You will not find it in your settings. It is hidden. To \\"unlock\\" it, here's what you have to do: Go to Settings, then go to About Device then scroll down to Build Number and tap it 7 times (I later heard you can tap 5 times, but I did 7). You'll get a little pop up saying that you have enabled developer mode. You can now debug USB, etc.....just when I thought I was getting to the meat of the phone, I discover all these other things. I'm going to keep searching, I might even find a personal cloaking device in here! ;)

One more thing, be careful with contact info. I accidently merged two accounts, and so one was deleted. I had to manually re-enter it.

Original:
It's nice to have a phone with such a large, brite screen....especially when your eyes aren't as good as they used to be. We had iPhone 5's and they were fine, but there was a lot missing. Let me first tell you that the phone is pretty amazing, but also has some quirks. I am not an Apple hater (we have several ipads, including 2 mini's), and I was tempted to stay with the iphones, however, since we were able to upgrade, we thought we'd give it a chance. Keep in mind that I used to have a Samsung Brightside (dumb phone) and I HATED it, so it was tough to get these.

Obviously, the ability to throw in a 64 gig card, pull it out, and put everything onto my computer/external drive, etc., and I have to say, it is very convenient. Another wonderful thing is the battery. It lasts a long, Imean LONG, time. One thing to note, if you let it drop to below 15% charge, it says that it could effect how well

product_title: LEPOWER MFI Apple Certified 2400 mAh Battery Case charger for iPhone 5 5S, Rechargeable & Portable Extended backup power bank for iPhone 5 5S
review_body: I bought this case and charger because I saw several people at work with it and thought that it might be a good option for my business iPhone. The design has several major drawbacks. One, it is somewhat bulky and the hard plastic and rounded back makes is difficult to hold and slippery. In fact, I'm surprised that I haven't dropped it yet. Another major flaw is that the case covers up the charging port on the bottom of the iPhone and uses a separate plug that comes with the case. This means that you can't use your standard charger and have to carry around another plug when you travel - this may only be an issue for me because I carry two iPhones, one personal and one for business but I now need two different chargers. With this alternate charging port, it's a little odd because it seems like you are not directly charging your phone, you charge the case and then transfer the power from the case to the phone. This seems inefficient because I would prefer to keep the extra battery charged and just directly charge the phone, only using the backup power from the phone when needed. It's also possible that I am using the charger the wrong way but it is difficult to tell because it came with almost no instructions.

product_title: Garmin nÃ¼vi 5-Inch Portable Vehicle GPS
review_headline: You can make lemonade from this one!
review_body:
Right out of the box, the software to upgrade maps did not work. Didn't send it back in time, so ended up using it. I live in a rural area, and it more-often-than-not cannot find a satellite until I get near a town. But the major problem with it is that the light goes out automatically (as an energy-saving feature, I suppose) after only a few minutes and then will not come back on. It is supposed to light back up if you touch it, but it doesn't. I went into the settings and set it to NEVER automatically turn off, but it still turns off after about 1 minute. You cannot see the map without the light. The only way to use this GPS is to pull over, turn it off, turn it back on, plug in the directions again, and then try to memorize where to go before the light turns off again. I can pull off the road with a paper road atlas and get the directions faster with a lot less frustration.
I had an inexpensive Garmin that was hard to read but worked well for 3 years; it was stolen. This was supposed to be an upgrade. I can't imagine why anyone would give this lemon a good review.

product_title: Qstarz BT-Q818XT 10Hz 66 Channel Bluetooth GPS Receiver
review_body:
Used it with my Android phone and the Trackmaster application as a datalogger for both Autocross and track racing. You can see results of the telemetry on Youtube on the frogracingvideos channel.
The GPS has 2 settings (1Hz and 10Hz) but you can reprogram it easily to do 5Hz (either 1Hz/5Hz or 5Hz/10Hz) if you use a program that can only use a 5Hz stream. The program needed is available for download from the Qstarz web site. Bluetooth connection is a breeze(use 0000 for passcode during pairing).
You can recharge the embedded battery through USB or with an external charger that is provided. The battery seems to be big enough to last a full day of racing. Highly recommended for those who want a cheap data logging solution for racing.
